    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <head>No. 56<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Foreign Ministers of the United States,
                            the United Kingdom, and France</gloss> to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Chancellor of the Federal Republic</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d56fn1">Source: Reprinted from <hi
                            rend="italic">Senate Q and <gloss target="#t_R1">R</gloss>
                        </hi>, p. 151.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-26">May 26,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Chancellor</hi>: The Three Powers advise you that, in
                    the exercise of their rights relating to Berlin and to Germany as a whole,
                    including the unification of Germany and a peace settlement, referred to in
                    Article 2 of the Convention on Relations between the Three Powers and the
                    Federal Republic of Germany,<note n="2" xml:id="d56fn2">
                        <ref target="#d51">Document 51</ref>.</note> they will require that the
                    following legislation of the Control Council be not deprived of effect in the
                    Federal territory by the Federal Republic: Proclamation No. 1 and Directives
                    Nos. 1, 2, 4–7, 11–13, 17, 20, 21, 34, 36, 42, 43, 49, 51 and 53.</p>
                <p>Nothing in this letter is intended to or shall be construed as modifying in any
                    way the new relations between the Three Powers and the Federal Republic
                    established by the Convention on Relations between the Three Powers and the
                    Federal Republic of Germany and the related Conventions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dean Acheson</hi>
                                </persName>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, United States of America</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Schuman</hi>
                                </persName>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Minister of the Republic of France</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Anthony Eden</hi>
                                </persName>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Her Britannic Majesty’s Principal Secretary of
                                    State for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
